name: NSUUID
desc: An object representing a universally unique value that bridges to UUID; use NSUUID when you need reference semantics or other Foundation-specific behavior.

items.name: init()
items.desc: Initializes a new UUID with RFC 4122 version 4 random bytes.

items.name: init?(uuidString: String)
items.desc: Initializes a new UUID with the formatted string.

items.name: init(uuidBytes: UnsafePointer<UInt8>?)
items.desc: Initializes a new UUID with the given bytes.
